The paper deals with the characterization of error and erasure correction, and information leakage in linear network coding, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. It also discusses the similarities between generalized rank and Hamming weights, which are commonly used in cryptography and coding theory, and thus could also be classified under the sub-categories of cryptography (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
